summary: I watched the first episode of Moominvalley
title: I watched the first episode of Moominvalley
body:
(Spoilery review under the cut!)

Animation and style-wise it was beautiful and almost perfect (the Moomin mouths were a bit awkward due to their big snouts). Sadly since I never liked Mymble and her kids (except Little My, obviously) I wasn’t as invested as I could’ve been. The plotline of “pretend it’s Midsummer so Mymble would leave” was kinda dumb, and when Moomintrolls “house” sank completely in beach sand I had to collect myself from the weirded out feeling. Also it was painfully obvious at times that the show was dubbed (the original language is English, I watched it in Finnish), especially when a couple of the voices I heard have voice acted in a half a billion other shows. 

The plotline MAY have come from the comics which I’ve never read, so that might’ve been a hindrance to my enjoyment as well.

Still, I liked it. Still waiting for my childhood crush. 

Which reminds me:

SNIFF IS MY DARLING BABY AND I WILL LOVE HIM FOREVER! KEEP YOUR SNUFKINS, SNIFF IS MINE!

(jk)*

*Not really.

summary: Okay, it was first episode, so my mind can change. But after that first episode my judgment is that it was okay. It’s not like...
body:
Okay, it was first episode, so my mind can change. But after that first episode my judgment is that it was okay. It’s not like old Moomin and it never will be, and I really shouldn’t compare this new series to it, but I do. Old Moomin is so much better. But yeah, it was only one episode, so it’s very possible that my mind can change.

There were funny moments. Satu Silvo is very good as Moominmamma (almost like Ulla Tapaninen). Good choice, good choice.

Moomins mouths were fuckin’ weird, tho. I mean, they showed them many times and it was a little bit creepy.

There wasn’t theme song. Why? Will there be? I hope so.

All the same, it was good. I will definitely watch the next episode next Monday.

Tho, they did something that is very unforgivable. They made me hate Little My for a minute! Like what the hell?! Any other version, not the originals or adaptions, have never made me hate her even for a sec (not even then when MTV3 ruined the voices). But this version did. And that is unforgivable. Okay, Little My is been my favourite character forever since ever, I’ve always loved her and I’ll always love her. So fuck you making me hate her for a teeny-tiny moment. I will never forgive it.

So, Snufkin will be in the next episode? Cool, cool. Can’t wait to hear Olavi Uusivirta as Snufkin. I’m pretty sure he’s perfect choice.
